  <prompt>
    Update `docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md` to add ONE line in the code review checklist section per FR-24: "Verify test-update obligation per `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`."

    Per design.md §5.5 anti-drift enforcement (locked decision 2026-05-30), the code review checklist line is the third of three coordinated mechanisms: (1) `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` "Test update obligation" section (task 080), (2) PR template question (task 081), (3) THIS code review checklist line (task 082). All three reference each other.

    Soft dependency on task 080: the checklist line cites the constraint document section. If task 080 has not yet shipped at execution time, this task ships the checklist line self-contained and task 080 fulfills the reference later.

    NO production code changes. Single line addition to an existing procedure document.
  </prompt>

  <role>AI agent adding a single code-review-checklist line to enforce anti-drift governance.</role>

  <goal>
    `docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md` updated with ONE new line in the code review checklist section: "Verify test-update obligation per `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`."

    The line is placed in the existing code review checklist section (likely a bullet list). Existing procedure sections preserved unchanged. The line is a single bullet, not a sub-section — owner direction was "do not over-burden PR process."
  </goal>

