  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md §5.5 and §6.6 (existing test conventions honored), the code review checklist line is one of three coordinated anti-drift mechanisms. The line is intentionally a single bullet — owner direction was "do not over-burden PR process" — and a more elaborate addition would diffuse the rule. Reviewers check this line per PR; the heavy lifting (what the obligation IS) lives in the constraint file referenced by the line. The existing `docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md` likely has a "code review" or "checklist" section; the new line drops there.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="080" status="not-started">Soft — checklist line cites `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` "Test update obligation" section. If 080 hasn't shipped, this task lands self-contained; task 080 fulfills the reference target later.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
